{"event": "dialogue", "npc": "Warden Cael", "speaker": "cael", "text": "Thank the Rootstones, a traveler! I am Warden Cael of the Rootwarden Circle. Please — I need help. The Thornpillar is dimming, and three of our monitoring stations have gone silent. Are you willing to assist?", "choices": [{"index": 0, "text": "What is the Thornpillar?"}, {"index": 1, "text": "What happened to the monitoring stations?"}, {"index": 2, "text": "I'll help. What do I need to do?"}, {"index": 3, "text": "I have other matters to attend to."}]}
{"event": "dialogue_choice", "npc": "Warden Cael", "selected": {"index": 0, "text": "What is the Thornpillar?"}}
{"event": "dialogue", "npc": "Warden Cael", "speaker": "cael", "text": "The Thornpillar is one of the great Rootstones — a massive crystalline formation that reaches from deep below into the sky above us. The Rootstones are what hold the Shards of Aethermoor aloft above the Underlurk abyss. Without them, everything falls. The Thornpillar is the one nearest to Greyhollow. It is the one that is dying.", "choices": [{"index": 0, "text": "What do you mean, dying?"}, {"index": 1, "text": "Tell me about the monitoring stations."}, {"index": 2, "text": "I've heard enough. I'll help."}]}
{"event": "dialogue_choice", "npc": "Warden Cael", "selected": {"index": 0, "text": "What do you mean, dying?"}}
{"event": "dialogue", "npc": "Warden Cael", "speaker": "cael", "text": "Its resonance is decreasing. The light output has dropped fourteen percent in the last three months — which sounds small, but the rate is accelerating. We have monitoring stations that measure the crystalline output and transmit resonance data. Three of those stations went silent eight days ago. Without their data, we cannot determine the rate or cause. That is what I need — someone to investigate what happened at each station and retrieve the data crystals.", "choices": [{"index": 0, "text": "Where are the stations?"}, {"index": 1, "text": "Why can't you do this yourself?"}, {"index": 2, "text": "I'll take the job."}]}
{"event": "dialogue_choice", "npc": "Warden Cael", "selected": {"index": 0, "text": "Where are the stations?"}}
{"event": "dialogue", "npc": "Warden Cael", "speaker": "cael", "text": "Station Verath is in the north foothills, a short climb above Greyhollow. Station Ossian is harder — you'll need to enter the cave network directly beneath the Thornpillar. And Station Keld is on the eastern ridge, about three hours on foot. I'm marking them on your map now.", "choices": [{"index": 0, "text": "What should I expect inside?"}, {"index": 1, "text": "I have what I need. I'll go now."}]}
{"event": "dialogue_choice", "npc": "Warden Cael", "selected": {"index": 0, "text": "What should I expect inside?"}}
{"event": "dialogue", "npc": "Warden Cael", "speaker": "cael", "text": "Normally? Monitoring equipment and maybe some cave spiders. Currently? I genuinely don't know. The stations are hardened against weather but not against people with ill intent. Bring a torch and something sharp.", "choices": [{"index": 0, "text": "Good advice. I'll head out now."}]}
{"event": "dialogue_choice", "npc": "Warden Cael", "selected": {"index": 0, "text": "Good advice. I'll head out now."}}
{"event": "dialogue", "npc": "Warden Cael", "speaker": "cael", "text": "Thank you. The three stations are marked on your map. Retrieve the resonance collector crystals from each one and bring them to Elder Sathis at the Rootwarden Sanctuary in the Aetherwood. I can't pay much, but the Rootwarden Circle will be in your debt. And at the moment, that debt matters.", "choices": [{"index": 0, "text": "I'll return when I have the samples."}]}
{"event": "dialogue_choice", "npc": "Warden Cael", "selected": {"index": 0, "text": "I'll return when I have the samples."}}
